  "title": "A Lesson Set in Stones",
  "summary": "Aboard the freighter White Ghost, the dark Force-user Simon prepares to give his two new initiates, the wiry Mira and the silver-haired Corellian Markus, their first joint lesson after Markus returns from an errand on Coruscant. Mira proudly demonstrates that she has taught herself to make small rocks roll using the True Source, and Simon invites Markus to show what he has discovered in turn -- sensing the direction a rock moves without being told. Pleased yet wary, Simon reflects privately that training them is like handing infants sharp knives, and he reminds them that there is a deeper lesson beyond merely moving stones or seeing the unseen. When Markus admits he cannot grasp the underlying point, Simon reassures him and turns the conversation toward the nature of their power, explaining that what they call the True Source is known where they come from as the Force -- the subject he most wants to teach them.",
